The LATEX code to draw a FEN notation of a chessboard would include the required packages such as `forsyth` or `xboard`. The following code would draw the board in its initial state:

\begin{code}
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{forsyth}
\usepackage{xboard}

\begin{document}

\begin{xboard}
  \setlength{\extralength}{8mm}
  \setlength{\intrength}{8mm}
  \setlength{\hugextrawidth}{12mm}
  \setlength{\hugextratitle}{3mm}
  \setlength{\intrighttitle}{5mm}
  \setlength{\intrightsym}{$\huge\Box$}
  \setlength{\extralighttitle}{0mm}
  \setlength{\extralightsym}{$\huge\bullet$}
  \setlength{\intrightangle}{45}
  \setlength{\extralightangle}{135}
  \begin{displayboard}
  \setlength{\intrightsym}{$\huge\Box$}
  \setlength{\intrighttitle}{5mm}
  \setlength{\intrightangle}{45}
  \setlength{\extralightsym}{$\huge\bullet$}
  \setlength{\extralighttitle}{0mm}
  \setlength{\extralightangle}{135}
  \end{displayboard}
\end{xboard}

\end{document}
\end{code}

